
[1]scarecrow

   SCARECROW, n. [scarce and crow.]

   1. Any frightful thing set up to frighten crows or other fowls from
   corn fields; hence, any thing terrifying without danger; a vain terror.

   A scarecrow set to frighten fools away.

   2. A fowl of the sea gull kind; the black gull.
